  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Since we have External WDG in Aurix convergence projects, it is important that we need make sure any internal Reset in SCC should not end in a double reset by external WDG"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "FSP connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "When any one of the Reset pins of external WDG is asserted, WDG monitoring functionality of external WDG will be disabled",
        "FSP0 pin is connected to IN2 of external WDG and IN2 has direct mapping with Reset2 pin."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/FSP%20Handling%20-%20SCC%20Reset%20control/image2023-1-9_10-44-25.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/FSP Handling - SCC Reset control/image2023-1-9_10-44-25.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Below picture shows the FSP pin control"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/FSP%20Handling%20-%20SCC%20Reset%20control/image2023-1-9_10-46-59.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/FSP Handling - SCC Reset control/image2023-1-9_10-46-59.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "So, at startup, FSP will be in asserted state which means external WDG functionality will be disabled, only when ReleaseFSP is called, external WDG functionality will start."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Open points:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "@Luo Ellen"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "At which point Safety module will release FSP ?",
        "When there is an issue with SM52 we will assert FSP, at this time external WDG will be disabled. Is this ok from Safety view?"
      ]
    }
  ],
